<HEADLINE> Clinton Arrives in Germany for Visit </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BERLIN, June 1 (Xinhua) -- U.S. President Bill Clinton arrived
at Tegel airport in Berlin on Thursday afternoon for a three-day
visit to Germany.
</P>
<P>
Clinton is expected to meet German President Johannes Rau,
Chancellor Gerhard Schroeder as well as former chancellor Helmut
Kohl.
</P>
<P>
He will also attend a 14-nation summit, which will focus on "
Progressive Governance for the 21st century."
</P>
<P>
Germany is the second leg of Clinton's European tour. He is
scheduled to travel to Moscow on Saturday to meet new Russian
President Vladimir Putin. 
</P>
</TEXT>
