<HEADLINE> Xinhua World News Summary at 1600 GMT, June 1 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING -- Kim Jong Il, general secretary of the Central
Committee of the Workers' Party of the Democratic People's
Republic of Korea (DPRK), and chairman of DPRK's National Defense
Commission, concluded his three-day unofficial visit to China on
Wednesday, a spokesman of the International Department of the
Central Committee of the Communist Party of China (CPC) announced
here Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Beginning his visit on May 29, Kim was invited by Jiang Zemin,
general secretary of the CPC Central Committee and president of
China. (DPRK-China-Visit)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
JERUSALEM -- U.S. Secretary of State Madeleine Albright is
scheduled to arrive in Middle East on Monday in an effort to "
narrow the gap" between Israel and the Palestinians in final-
status negotiations.
</P>
<P>
The visit was announced by United States President Bill Clinton
Thursday in Lisbon, Portugal, after his meeting there with Israeli
Prime Minister Ehud Barak.
</P>
<P>
Barak, flew to Lisbon especially for the meeting with Clinton,
will rush back to Israel later in the day. (U.S.-Middle East-Visit)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
BERLIN -- U.S. President Bill Clinton arrived in Berlin's Tegel
Airport on Thursday afternoon to make a three-day visit to Germany.
</P>
<P>
President Clinton will meet with the German Federal President
Johannes Rau in Schloss Bellevue, the German presidential palace.
Then he will make talks with the German Chancellor Gerhard
Schroeder in Kanzleramt on the Schlossplatz.
</P>
<P>
His most important activity is attending the summit conference
of the "Modern Government of the 21st Century" from June 2 to 3 in
Schloss Charlottenburg in Berlin. 
</P>
</TEXT>
