<HEADLINE> (Update) Crash Kills Four in Moscow, Famous Eye Doctor Among Dead  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, June 2 (Xinhua) -- Four people were killed Friday when
a helicopter crashed in northwest Moscow. Famous eye surgeon
Svyatoslav Fyodorov was identified as among the victims.
</P>
<P>
Fyodorov is known for his contributions to eye microsurgery.
The aircraft is believed to belong to Foydorov's clinic.
</P>
<P>
The eye surgeon reportedly acquired a license for piloting a
helicopter only recently.
</P>
<P>
All four victims died instantly when the helicopter crashed
onto wasteland near Svetlogorsky Proyezd at about 7:45 p.m. local
time(15:45 GMT).
</P>
<P>
Fyodorov's wife and members of his clinics' staff identified
him, the Itar-Tass news agency reported, quoting First Deputy
Interior Minister Nikolai Solovyov.
</P>
<P>
The make of the ill-fated chopper was not immediately known,
but Solovyov it was foreign made. 
</P>
</TEXT>
