<BODY>
<HEADLINE> 500,000 Cuban Women Demand Elian's Return </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Mothers, grandmothers, working women and housewives shouted
slogan "down with the lies, return our Elian."
</P>
<P>
The protest is the reaction to the 11th U.S. Circuit Court of
Appeals in Atlanta's decision on the case of Elian.
</P>
<P>
The 11th U.S. Circuit Court of Appeals in Atlanta ruled that
Elian was not entitled to a political asylum hearing as his U.S.
relatives had sought. But the court did not let the boy return
immediately to Cuba as his father and other relatives in Cuba have
demanded.
</P>
<P>
The boy and his father currently are residing together in
Washington with some other relatives and friends, waiting for
permission from U.S. authorities to return to Cuba.
</P>
<P>
Elian was rescued at sea in November after his boat capsized,
killing his mother and 10 other illegal Cuban migrants.
</P>
<P>
Elian's father, a tourism worker from the provincial Cuban
town of Cardenas, has demanded his son's return from the start and
was reunited with the boy in Washington in April after a dramatic
raid on the Miami house of the boy's U.S. relatives. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
