<HEADLINE> German Economy Minister Starts Visit to Cuba </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HAVANA, June 2 (Xinhua) -- German Federal State Economy and
Technology Minister Mathias Gabriel started Friday a four-day
working visit to Cuba.
</P>
<P>
Gabriel, who arrived Thursday night in Havana, met Friday with
Government Minister Ricardo Cabrisas and with Vice Minister of
Foreign Trade Orlando Hernandez Guillen, with whom he exchanged
ideas about cooperation perspectives.
</P>
<P>
The two countries could cooperate in the areas of industry, of
citrus fruits, and of basic industry, among others. The German
official showed interest in cooperating with Cuba in the
production of steel, alternate energy sources, and sugar.
</P>
<P>
Gabriel has in his agenda meetings with Vice President Carlos
Lage and with officials of the agriculture and sugar ministries.
</P>
</TEXT>
