<HEADLINE> Israeli Boy Freed From Captivity </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, June 2 (Xinhua) -- Russian law enforcement agents set
free a 13-year-old Israeli boy Thursday from more than nine months
of captivity, said Russian media reports Friday.
</P>
<P>
Adi Sharon, kidnapped on August 23 last year, was rescued in a
summer resort settlement near Penza, a city in central-west Russia.
The kidnappers had demanded an 8 million U.S. dollar ransom for
him.
</P>
<P>
Russian television showed an emaciated Sharon shaking, with his
small fingers of both hands cut off by the kidnappers. He is
receiving intensive therapy in a Moscow hospital.
</P>
<P>
Twelve men were detained in the operation conducted by the
Interior Ministry's Department for Combating Organized Crime, nine
of them in Moscow, two in Penza and one in Ingushetia. Six of the
detained are Chechens, the rest are Russians, the Interfax news
agency reported. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
