disputes, including the concerns of tribe chiefs in KwaZulu-Natal
Province that their powers may be reduced in the new local
government system.
</P>
<P>
In this regard, Mchunu said the commission is working with all
stakeholders to ensure that "all were comfortable" with the
elections.
</P>
<P>
On the question of special votes and the right of prisoners to
vote, Director-General of the Provincial Affairs and Local
Government Department Zam Titus said the matter will be discussed
at a special meeting in Parliament next Monday. 
