<BODY>
<HEADLINE> 1,4000 Foreign Women Become Sex Slaves in UK Each Year </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, June 2 (Xinhua) -- Up to 1,400 foreign women were
tricked into sexual slavery in Britain each year, according to a
report commissioned by the Home Office.
</P>
<P>
Organized gangs were forcing women, increasingly drawn from
Eastern Europe, into prostitution because it was a lucrative and
low-risk activity, the report said.
</P>
<P>
Vice detectives in London said the women suffer threats and
intimidation which makes the situation increasingly difficult to
police.
</P>
<P>
But researchers said most police forces adopt a "hands off"
approach to prostitution and will usually only act after
complaints from the public, the BBC reported on Friday.
</P>
<P>
Dr. Liz Kelly and Dr. Linda Regan of the University of North
London's Child and Women Abuse Studies Centre, said the increase
in the numbers of women trafficked around the world was a "major
concern".
</P>
<P>
Their study - the first of its kind to assess the extent of the
problem - highlights the difficulty of accurately saying how many
women are brought into Britain for prostitution.
</P>
<P>
But following interviews with experts, a survey of police
forces and official figures they estimated that between 140 and 1,
400 women were used as sex slaves each year in the UK. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
