<HEADLINE> Crash Kills Four in Moscow, Paper of Famous Eye Doctor Found </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, June 2 (Xinhua) -- Four people were killed Friday when
a helicopter crashed in northwest Moscow. Documents of famous eye
surgeon Svyatoslav Fyodorov were found at the site.
</P>
<P>
In addition to the papers, an artificial limb was also found,
the Interfax news agency reported.
</P>
<P>
Fyodorov is known for his contributions to eye microsurgery.
</P>
<P>
With both his legs partially amputated, Fyodorov is known to
have used artificial limbs, Interfax said.
</P>
<P>
However, there has been no official confirmation from law
enforcement agencies whether Fyodorov was among the four victims,
who died instantly when the helicopter crashed onto wasteland near
Svetlogorsky Proyezd at about 7:45 p.m. local time (15:45 GMT).
</P>
<P>
A Red Cross and a sign for Fyodorov's polyclinic were painted
on the helicopter's fuselage. 
</P>
</TEXT>
