<HEADLINE> Some White People Ready to Leave Zimbabwe </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HARARE, June 2 (Xinhua) -- An increasing number of white
Zimbabweans are ready to go abroad by clearing their vehicles as
they anticipate an escalation in political violence ahead of the
parliamentary elections scheduled for June 24-25.
</P>
<P>
Harare provincial police spokeswoman Tendai Nembire told the
Zimbabwe News Agency Friday that there had been a sharp increase
in the number of white people clearing their vehicles.
</P>
<P>
In May alone, a total of 3,001 vehicles from the white
community were cleared compared with 540 during the same period
last year, she said.
</P>
<P>
Most of the whites who cleared their vehicles said that they
were going for holidays and would come back after elections as
they feared political violence.
</P>
<P>
Travel agencies told the national news agency that most of the
whites intended to leave for South Africa at least a week before
the elections. Some will fly to Australia, Britain and New Zealand
among the countries they consider safe.
</P>
<P>
"I think they are being influenced from some quarter as I
cannot see the reason why they are fleeing in such large numbers.
There are no problems from black foreigners as they are not
panicking," she added.
</P>
<P>
Zimbabwe has been gripped by a wave of political violence
related to farm invasion and the coming elections, in which at
least 20 people, including five white farmers and opposition party
candidates and supporters, were killed. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
