<HEADLINE> Mongolian Province on Alert for Anthracnose </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ULAN BATOR, June 2 (Xinhua) -- Mongolia's Dornod Province is on
high alert after a case of anthracnose was confirmed Thursday,
Mongolian News Agency reported Friday.
</P>
<P>
The provincial authorities on Friday announced a ban on the
transport and sales of meat, milk and hide. Road checks were
ordered.
</P>
<P>
A woman in Herlen county of the province was found ill last
Saturday after eating meat. She was found infected with
anthracnose on Thursday. 
