<HEADLINE> Lanfranchi Wins 19th Stage at Tour of Italy </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ROME, June 2 (Xinhua) -- Paolo Lanfranchi of Italy won the 19th
stage while his compatriot Francesco Casagrande retained the
overall leader's pink jersey at the Tour of Italy cycling race on
Friday.
</P>
<P>
Unheralded Lanfranchi put up a solo finish to win the stage,
beating second-placed Marco Pantani of Italy by nearly one minute.
</P>
<P>
Lanfranchi covered the 176-kilometer stage from Saluzzo to
Briancon in five hours 32 minutes and 7 seconds. Pantani finished
second, with 54 seconds behind.
</P>
<P>
Casagrande held a 25 seconds lead going into Saturday's 34-
kilometer time trial from Briancon to Sestriere. 
</P>
</TEXT>
