<HEADLINE> Today's Diplomatic News Highlights </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 2 (Xinhua) -- Following are highlights of today's
diplomatic news released by Xinhua:
</P>
<P>
 Vice-President Meets Kyrgyzstan Defense Minister
</P>
<P>
Chinese Vice-President Hu Jintao met with Kyrgyzstan Defense
Minister Esen Topoyev and his party here today.
</P>
<P>
Hu, also vice-chairman of the Central Military Commission, said
the two countries are good neighbors linked by rivers and
mountains, and noted that relations between the two countries and
armed forces have been developing well, and cooperation at
bilateral and multilateral levels has yielded positive results,
thanks to the efforts made by the leaders of the two countries.
</P>
<P>
China highly values the great importance the Kyrgyzstan
government gives to developing bilateral relations, and its
consistent support for China on the issue of Taiwan and its
opposition to national separatism, Hu said.
</P>
<P>
 Beijing Party Chief Meets Japanese Guest
</P>
<P>
Jia Qinglin, a member of the Political Bureau of the Communist
Party of China Central Committee and secretary of the Beijing
Municipal Party Committee, met here today with former Governor
Isamu Takada of Japan's Nagasaki Prefecture.
</P>
<P>
Jia extended a warm welcome to Takada and praised him as an old
friend of the Chinese people, who has long been working for the
relationship between the two countries.
</P>
<P>
He expressed the hope that Takada will come to Beijing more
often to help promote exchanges between the Chinese capital and
Nagasaki in all fields.
</P>
<P>
Indian President Visits China's Yunnan Province
</P>
<P>
Indian President Kocheril Raman Narayanan said here this
evening that there's potential to explore and develop cooperation
between India and China's Yunnan Province.
</P>
<P>
The visiting Indian President told Governor Li Jiating of south-
west China's Yunnan Province that there is broad cooperative
prospects in fields such as high-technology, software, and mineral
processing.
</P>
<P>
He said Yunnan is close to India both geographically and
culturally, and there are long-term economic and cultural contacts
between them.
</P>
<P>
Senior Party Official Leaves to Visit Four Nordic Countries
</P>
<P>
Ding Guangen, head of the Department of Publicity of the
Central Committee of the Communist Party of China (CPC), left here
Friday morning on a good-will visit to four Nordic Countries.
</P>
<P>
Ding, also a member of the Political Bureau and Secretariat of
the CPC Central Committee, is paying the visit to Denmark, Sweden,
Iceland and Norway, at the invitation of the governments of the
four countries.
</P>
<P>
China Makes Representations to the Philippines on Killing of
Fisherman
</P>
<P>
The Chinese Foreign Ministry will make further representations
to the Philippines on compensation for the incident in which a
Chinese fishing boat was attacked and one fisherman was shot dead
by Philippine maritime police in the South China Sea, according to
ministry sources today. 
</P>
</TEXT>
