<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Jiang Congratulates Chang Hsueh-liang on 100th Birthday </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, June 2 (Xinhua) -- Chinese President Jiang Zemin on
Thursday congratulated General Chang Hsueh-liang on the occasion
of his 100th birthday. Jiang also sent him a basket of flowers.
</P>
<P>
"On the occasion of your 100th birthday, I am sending this
message to extend my heartfelt congratulations," said Jiang.
</P>
<P>
"Your outstanding historic contributions, which will definitely
shine through the ages, have been admired and remembered by
Chinese people both home and abroad. Your patriotic spirit will no
doubt be carried forward.
</P>
<P>
"I hope you would take good care of yourself and lead a happy
life."
</P>
<P>
The message and the flowers were delivered to Chang on Thursday
by the Chinese consulate-general in Hawaii.
</P>
<P>
Chang told acting Consular-General Xu Shiguo that he is very
happy to receive the message and flowers from Jiang. He asked Xu
to convey his heartfelt gratitude to Jiang.
</P>
<P>
Li Ruihuan, chairman of the National Committee of the Chinese
People's Political Consultative Conference, also sent a
congratulatory letter to Chang. 
</P>
</TEXT>
