<DATE_TIME> 2000-06-02 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> E. Coli Toll May have Reached 11 in Canada: Officials </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
OTTAWA, June 2 (Xinhua) -- The E. coli toll may have reached 11,
said Canadian health officials Thursday in the southern Ontario
town of Walkerton.
</P>
<P>
Authorities have confirmed the deaths of seven E. coli victims.
They are still investigating four more deaths to determine whether
or not they were linked to the worst outbreak of the deadly
disease in the country.
</P>
<P>
The latest four deaths were reported to provincial police on
Wednesday and Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Walkerton is in its third week of E. coli infection, which has
struck up to 1,000 people in the farm town of 5,000.
</P>
<P>
Residents of the town may have to wait another eight weeks
before they can be sure that the town's water supply is free of
the deadly E. coli bacteria, local health officials say. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
