<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Seminar on Western China Development Slated for Chongqing </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHONGQING, June 2 (Xinhua) -- The International Seminar on
Development of Western China is scheduled to be held in Chongqing
on June 8-10, the organizer announced here today.
</P>
<P>
The seminar has invited 100 celebrated experts, scholars, and
politicians from the United States, Britain, Russia, Japan, France,
Germany, Australia, and Canada including Lawrence Klein, a Nobel
laureate, Bob Hawke, former prime minister of Australia, and K.
Remchukov, vice-chairman of the Committee of Natural Resources of
the State Duma of Russia. Also on hand will be representatives of
a dozen of the 500 top multinational corporations and
international organizations.
</P>
<P>
The seminar is jointly sponsored by the Chongqing Municipal
Government, the United Nations Development Program (UNDP), the
Chinese Academy of Social Sciences, and the Ministry of Foreign
Trade and Economic Cooperation.
</P>
<P>
With the theme: gearing up for economic globalization in the
21st century and developing western China, the seminar will
emphasize four topics including the government's role in regional
development and narrowing regional disparity.
</P>
<P>
The Three Gorges International Tourism Festival will be held
simultaneously in Chongqing, and the city is busy preparing for
the two events. Tens of thousands of volunteers have offered their
services, and many are attending translation and diplomatic
ceremony training courses.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
