<HEADLINE> Chinese President Writes Inscription for World Computing Conference </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 2 (Xinhua) -- President Jiang Zemin has written
an inscription for the 16th World Computing Conference, extending
his wishes for the success of the event.
</P>
<P>
The conference, to be held in Beijing on August 21-25, was
sponsored by the United Nations Educational, Scientific and
Cultural Organization (UNESCO) and is held every two years. China
acquired the right to host the 2000 conference in 1995.
</P>
<P>
Officials revealed that preparation work is running smoothly.
More than 50 experts from around the world will take part in the
conference which has received 2,500 essays.
</P>
<P>
An exhibition and a computing contest for middle-school
students will be held during the conference. 
</P>
</TEXT>
