<HEADLINE> Shanghai, Hong Kong to Enhance Cooperation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, June 2 (Xinhua) -- Two key economic powerhouses of
China, Shanghai and Hong Kong should enhance their cooperation in
a number of areas, said Shanghai Mayor Xu Kuangdi at a metropolis
development symposium held here today.
</P>
<P>
Tung Chee Hwa, Chief Executive of China's Hong Kong Special
Administrative Region (SAR), who attended the symposium, said that
China's entry into the WTO will further improve such cooperation.
</P>
<P>
Tung also suggested that that Shanghai and Hong Kong will
participate in developing China's western regions.
</P>
<P>
A total of 250 deputies from Shanghai and Hong Kong attended
the Symposium. 
</P>
