<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Sichuan Province Faces New Population Problems </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHENGDU, June 2 (Xinhua) -- Populous Sichuan province in
southwest China will face increased pressures of population growth
as the number of child-bearing, aging populations and those
entering the workforce will peak in the next decade.
</P>
<P>
The third most populous province in China has more than 85.5
million people. Population in the province will grow to nearly 94
million around 2025.
</P>
<P>
The province has more than 23.5 million child-bearing women and
more than six million elderly. The current workforce exceeds 54
million, but there are only 46 million in employment. Some four
million are surplus workers in the province's rural areas.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
