<HEADLINE> HK Stock Exchange to Enhance Cooperation with Inland Counterparts </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, June 2 (Xinhua) -- Hong Kong Stock Exchange (HKSE)
aims to enhance cooperation with its inland counterparts, said
HKSE chairman Li Yeguang here today.
</P>
<P>
Li said that Hong Kong, Shanghai and Shenzhen stock exchanges
will establish an information platform serving investors both from
at home and abroad.
</P>
<P>
Li visited the Shanghai Stock Exchange today with Kuang Qizhi,
executive president of HKSE.
</P>
<P>
The chairman was optimistic about the future of the Shanghai
Stock Exchange. He said China's fast-growing economy and Shanghai
's unique status as the country's financial center are favorable
for the further developments. China's entry into the WTO will
undoubtedly provide more opportunities.  
</P>
