<HEADLINE> Heavy Rains Ease Drought In Central China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 2 (Xinhua) -- Drought in central China has been
alleviated since May 29 thanks to heavy rains, according to the
State Flood-Control and Drought-Relief Headquarters.
</P>
<P>
However, drought continues to plague north China. Statistics
show that a total of 10 million ha of field have been hit by
drought, and 17.7 million people and 14.9 million cattle do not
have enough water. 
</P>
</TEXT>
