<HEADLINE> China Tests Cellular Phones for Magnetic Radiation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 2 (Xinhua) -- Chinese industry authorities issued
certificates today on levels of magnetic radiation emitted from
Motorola China and Qingdao Haier cellular phones.
</P>
<P>
This is the first time that China conducted magnetic tests on
cellular phone products and issued certificates.
</P>
<P>
The move is designed to limit the level of magnetic radiation
of electronic devices produced in China. 
</P>
