<HEADLINE> Hi-Tech Fair to Improve Beijing's Image </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 2 (Xinhua) -- Beijing will develop the Beijing
International High-Tech Industry Week into an internationally
event, said Mayor Liu Qi today.
</P>
<P>
He asked the Beijing municipal government to develop a
comprehensive plan to turn the high-tech week into an
international fair as they prepare to host the annual event in
2001.
</P>
<P>
He made these remarks at a meeting on the Third China Beijing
International High-Tech Industry Week held last month.
</P>
<P>
He said that next year's event will draw more participants from
well-known international companies, organizations and universities.
The high-tech fair will provide numerous opportunities for both
large and small companies.
</P>
<P>
In order to facilitate Beijing's bid for the 2008 Olympic Games,
the fair will increase its display high-tech sports products.
</P>
</TEXT>
