<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Indian President Visits China's Yunnan Province </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUNMING, June 2 (Xinhua) -- Indian President Kocheril Raman
Narayanan said here this evening that there's potential to explore
and develop cooperation between India and China's Yunnan Province.
</P>
<P>
The visiting Indian President told Governor Li Jiating of south-
west China's Yunnan Province that there is broad cooperative
prospects in fields such as high-technology, software, and mineral
processing.
</P>
<P>
He said Yunnan is close to India both geographically and
culturally, and there are long-term economic and cultural contacts
between them.
</P>
<P>
Governor Li extended a warm welcome to the president,
explaining the rich natural and cultural resources in the province.
He also voiced the hope that cooperation would be further
developed in the transportation, tourist and mineral industries.
</P>
<P>
Narayanan arrived in Kunming yesterday evening from Dalian. He
visited different tourist spots in Kunming and held discussions
with local scholars today.  
</P>
</TEXT>
