<DOCNO> XIE20000602.0083 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-06-02 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Pakistan Plans to Slash Edible Oil Import </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, June 2 (Xinhua) -- The Pakistani government has
fixed a target of 1.46 million tons of domestic edible oil
production for the year 2000-2001 to slash 72 percent import bill
of the item.
</P>
<P>
An official from the Ministry of Food and Agriculture said
Friday that an area of 1.34 million acres will be cultivated in
the country in this regard.
</P>
<P>
The production target of edible oil for the year 2001-2002 (
July-June) has been proposed at 2.1 million tons to end the import
of edible oil.
</P>
<P>
Pakistan is also expecting to save a substantial amount of 500
million U.S. dollars during the current fiscal year, ending this
month, wing to reduction in its edible oil imports.
</P>
<P>
The ministry has stressed the need for production of hybrid
seed for sunflower, domestic certified seed for canola and compact
between farmers and solvent extraction industry to enhance the
domestic production and end import of edible oil.
</P>
<P>
The total requirement of edible oil in Pakistan during 1998-99
was 1.9 million tons of which only 0.5 million tons came from
local production and the rest were imported at a cost of 700
million dollars. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
