<HEADLINE> France Congratulates Luxembourg on Ending Hostage Crisis </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, June 2 (Xinhua) -- France congratulated Luxembourg
Friday on successfully ending a hostage crisis in a day-care
center in Wasserbillig, a small village in eastern Luxembourg.
</P>
<P>
"We are happy about the ending, and we thank the Luxembourg
government for their efficient handling of this grave crisis. We
are happy that all the hostages were freed without harm," said
French Foreign Ministry spokeswoman Anne Gazeau-Secret.
</P>
<P>
Luxembourg police Thursday shot and critically wounded the
hostage-taker, a 39-year-old man, and freed 25 children and three
teachers that were held hostage for 28 hours.
</P>
<P>
Among the hostages were four French children, three of them
possessing dual French-Luxembourg nationality. 
