<HEADLINE> Guo Takes First Gold for China at FINA Diving GP </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, June 2 (Xinhua) -- Guo Jingjing from diving
powerhouse China did not meet much trouble before winning the
first gold in the women's one-meter springboard at the Hong Kong
Diving Meet which opened here on Friday.
</P>
<P>
Guo Jingjing, now ranked first in the one-meter sprinboard in
China, was put in the second place to German Jane Smith after the
first two dives.
</P>
<P>
But she managed back to win the three divers' competition with
287.52 points.
</P>
<P>
"I am not satisfied with my performance today, especially the
first two dives," said Guo.
</P>
<P>
Jane Smith took the silver medal by collecting 254.64 points
while Tsai Yi Sam of Chinese Taipei finished third with 197.49
points.
</P>
<P>
The men's one-meter springboard title went to Dean Pullar of
Australia who
finished six dives with 335.94 points.
</P>
<P>
He beat Yu Yuet of Hong Kong, China, by a margin of 48.39
points. Yu ranked second and Lin Tze Hsiang from Chinese Taipei
took the bronz medal with 287.28 points.
</P>
<P>
The three-day meet, one of the 14-leg FINA Diving Grand Prix
series, will close on Sunday. 
</P>
</TEXT>
