<HEADLINE> Educational Aid To China's Western Regions </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 2 (Xinhua) -- Beijing plans to take a number of
educational measures to support the development of the county's
less developed western regions, according to the Beijing Education
Commission.
</P>
<P>
These measures include recruiting more students from these
regions, sending more qualified teachers to these regions and
providing more master or doctoral courses.
</P>
<P>
A local education official said colleges in Beijing this year
will recruit 80 percent more freshman from Inner Mongolia, one of
the poorest regions in China.
</P>
<P>
At the same time colleges in Beijing will also cooperate and
carry out exchange programs with their counterparts in these
regions. "Key laboratories in colleges in Beijing will open to
researchers from the China's west and there will be some 200
research projects in the next five years," the official said.
</P>
<P>
According to him, Beijing will also help to train over 2,000
teachers from western provinces in the next three to five years.
</P>
</TEXT>
