<HEADLINE> South China Province Holds Cosmetics Exposition </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUANGZHOU, June 2 (Xinhua) -- The 13th Guangdong International
Cosmetics Exposition was held today in Guangzhou, capital of south
China's Guangdong Province.
</P>
<P>
The four-day exposition covers an area of 30,000 square meters
and has attracted over 1,700 firms from 25 countries and regions.
</P>
<P>
China's cosmetics industry has witnessed rapid development in
the past few years. Statistics show that China currently has 2,500
cosmetics enterprises. Two thousand of them are in Guangdong.
</P>
<P>
Ma Ya, director of the Guangdong Hairdressing Association said
"each person in China spends only 20 yuan on cosmetics products
every year, while the per-capita consumption in developed country
is 80 U.S. dollars."
</P>
