<HEADLINE> All-China Federation of Taiwan Compatriots Issues Open Letter to People in Taiwan </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 2 (Xinhua) -- The All-China Federation of Taiwan
Compatriots issued an open letter to compatriots in Taiwan today.
</P>
<P>
The letter said that people from all walks of life in Taiwan
and Taiwan compatriots on the mainland are keeping a close eye on
the Taiwan Straits issue. Since Taiwan has a new leader, everyone
is hoping that relations between both sides of the straits will
turn around for the better.
</P>
<P>
However, the letter pointed out that the policy statement that
the new leader of Taiwan made and the comments that some new
members made in public have made compatriots disappointed and
anxious. Taiwan compatriots on the mainland share the same deep
worries as the people of Taiwan about the safety of their home and
lives.
</P>
<P>
The letter said that peaceful reunification of the motherland
cannot be postponed indefinitely. The Chinese people, including
23 million Taiwan compatriots, will not agree on the separation of
Taiwan from the motherland again.
</P>
<P>
The letter called for compatriots in Taiwan to stand up and
stop the activities of a handful of separatists. It also called
for Chinese all over the world to urge the new Taiwan authorities
to embrace peaceful reunification as soon as possible. 
</P>
</TEXT>
