<HEADLINE> 96 More to Run in HK Election Committee Subsector Polls </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, June 2 (Xinhua) -- The Registration and Electoral
Office of Hong Kong announced that 96 more persons had been
nominated to run in the Election Committee subsector elections
Friday, the third day of the nomination exercise.
</P>
<P>
The cumulative number of nominees is 345. So far the labor
subsector has the largest number of nominees, with 44, among the
35 subsectors, followed by the agriculture and fisheries subsector,
with 36, and the Chinese medicine subsector, with 33. There is no
nomination yet in the industrial subsector.
</P>
<P>
Nominations will close at 5 PM next Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The subsector elections have been scheduled for July 9 when 664
Election Committee members from 35 subsectors will be elected.
Each subsector is allocated seats ranging from 11 to 41.
</P>
<P>
The Election Committee will then elect six Legislative Council
members in the Legislative Council general election on September
10. 
</P>
