<HEADLINE> Hong Kong Stocks Close 2.30 Percent Higher </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, June 2 (Xinhua) -- Hong Kong stocks grew 342.91
points, or 2.30 percent, to close at 15,284.10 Friday.
</P>
<P>
Dealers said the market continued growing because of another
surge on Wall Street overnight.
</P>
<P>
Turnover totaled 12.599 billion HK dollars (1.615 billion U.S.
dollars), compared with Thursday's 11.669 billion HK dollars (1.
496 billion U.S. dollars).
</P>
<P>
Of the four sub-indices of Hang Seng Index, Finance, Utilities,
Properties and Commerce and Industry rose 0.17 percent, 0.52
percent, 4.80 percent and 2.94 percent, respectively.
</P>
<P>
The Hang Seng China Enterprises Index and the Hang Seng China-
Affiliated Corp Index gained 4.45 percent and 4.53 percent,
respectively.
</P>
<P>
The Hang Seng IT Index rose 3.59 percent and the Hang Seng IT
Portfolio Index 2.08 percent.
</P>
<P>
Hong Kong stocks increased 224.39 points, or 1.50 percent, to
open at 15,165.58 Friday and closed the morning session at 15,308.
86.
</P>
<P>
In the whole week, Hong Kong stocks rose 35.08 points, or 0.26
percent, to open at 13,757.78 on Monday and continued surging day
by day and closed at 15,284.10 on Friday. 
</P>
</TEXT>
