<HEADLINE> Air Services Agreement Signed Between HK, Norway </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, June 2 (Xinhua) -- The Government of the Hong Kong
Special Administrative Region (HKSAR) signed an air services
agreement on Friday with the Government of the Kingdom of Norway.
</P>
<P>
"We signed air services agreements with Denmark and Sweden
earlier this year. I am glad that we have now signed air services
agreements with all the three Scandinavian countries," said
Stephen Ip, secretary for economic services of HKSAR, at the
signing ceremony.
</P>
<P>
Ip said, "Although geographically far apart, Hong Kong and
Norway have established close links with each other."
</P>
<P>
"The conclusion of the air services agreement today is an
important milestone in our aviation relationship with Norway. At
present only all-cargo services are being operated between Hong
Kong and Scandinavia. I hope that passenger services will also be
operated soon," Ip added.
</P>
<P>
The agreement brings the number of air services agreements
signed by Hong Kong to 44. 
</P>
</TEXT>
