<BODY>
<HEADLINE> SAPE Holds Auction for Fund Raising </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 2 (Xinhua) -- An auction was held here today by
the Society of Avian Paleontology and Evolution (SAPE) to raise
funds.
</P>
<P>
The auction was part of the Fifth International Meeting of SAPE
and the Symposium on Jehol Biota, which both started yesterday
morning in Beijing.
</P>
<P>
All the items of the auction were donated by participants at
the meeting and symposium including rare fossils and books on
paleontology. Claws and teeth collected by the Natural History
Museum and Biodiversity Center Dyche Hall from the University of
Kansas were among the items auctioned.
</P>
<P>
SAPE was established in 1984 when the first meeting was held in
Paris and included the world's most well-known bird
paleontologists.
</P>
<P>
Auctions of this kind are held regularly by SAPE to raise funds
for the society as well as receiving donations from members.
</P>
<P>
More than 100 world known paleontologists are in Beijing to
discuss a number of topics on paleontology.  
</P>
</TEXT>
