<DOCNO> XIE20000602.0125 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-06-02 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Kuala Lumpur Stocks Close Lower </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUALA LUMPUR, June 2 (Xinhua) -- Share prices on the Kuala
Lumpur Stock Exchange closed lower Friday on the persistent
institutional selling on bluechip counters.
</P>
<P>
At the close, the 100-quality stocks Composite Index lost 13.28
points to 891.25, the all-share Emas Index eased 2.79 points to
225.15, the Industrial Index dipped 9.16 points to 1,574.8 and the
Second Board Index fell 3.17 points to 236.45.
</P>
<P>
Losers led gainers by 531 to 131 while 133 counters were
unchanged, 184 counters untraded and 61 others suspended.
</P>
<P>
The day's turnover stood at 147.635 million shares valued at
665.807 million ringgit (175.204 million U.S. dollars) against 131.
849 million shares worth 563.776 million ringgit (148.362 million
dollars) on Thursday. 
</P>
</TEXT>
