<HEADLINE> Indonesian President to Visit Portugal </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JAKARTA, June 2 (Xinhua) -- Indonesian President Abdurrahman
Wahid will visit Portugal in September, a senior official
confirmed here Friday.
</P>
<P>
President Wahid has accepted Portuguese President Jorge Sampaio
's invitation for the visit, Foreign Minister Alwi Shihab said
after a meeting between the president and Portuguese Foreign
Affairs Minister Jaime Gama at the Merdeka palace.
</P>
<P>
If president Wahid realized his plan to visit Portugal, it
would be a new phase in Indonesian-Portuguese relations, Shihab
said.
</P>
<P>
The relations between Indonesia and Portugal had been strained
until last year after East Timor -- a former Portuguese colony --
voted for independence from Indonesia.
</P>
<P>
East Timor integrated into Indonesia in 1976 following a
civilian war.
</P>
<P>
On December 28, 1999, Indonesia and Portugal normalized their
diplomatic relations which had been frozen by Lisbon in 1975 due
to the East Timor issue.
</P>
<P>
Shihab said he does not know the exact date of President Wahid'
s planned visit to Portugal.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, Gama said he was impressed with his meeting with
President Wahid, who believed that Indonesian-Portuguese ties will
further develop.
</P>
<P>
The two foreign ministers also held talks on a plan to sign
four agreements on general affairs, investment, social and
cultural affairs as well as double tax exemption.
</P>
<P>
Shihab said he believes that the new ties between Indonesia and
Portugal should start with a concrete cooperation in investment
and tourism. 
</P>
</TEXT>
