<HEADLINE> Share Prices Bounce Back on Singapore Stock Market </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The benchmark Straits Times Index (STI) shot up 73.14 points to
close at 1,910.40 points, bouncing back to the level above the 1,
900 mark
</P>
<P>
The total volume increased to 400.80 million shares valued at
747.67 million Singapore dollars (432.98 million U.S. dollars).
Gainers overwhelmed losers by 294 to 49 with 199 counters
unchanged.
</P>
<P>
GES topped the actives chart as it registered a turnover of 37.
22 million shares. It was followed by MediaRing, which had 24.72
million units done. Fastech was the next with 20.64 million
counters changing hands.
</P>
<P>
Creative 50 was the biggest gainer of the day skyrocketing by
190 cents to close at 45.40 Singapore dollars. DBS surged up 130
cents to finish at 19.40 Singapore dollars. Chartered ran up 120
cents to close at 15.50 Singapore dollars.
</P>
<P>
CMSPort headed the descent of the day shedding 40 cents to
close at 3.30 Hong Kong dollars. Ho GCen retreated 10 cents to
finish at 0.61 Singapore dollars. Jar Mat inched down eight cents
to end at 4.02 U.S. dollars.
</P>
<P>
Dealers said that Friday's upsurge came after Wall Street
rallied on hopes that interest rates may be close to their peak.
</P>
<P>
Brokers said interest rate sensitive stocks such as banks and
properties rose on the back of U.S. data showing a slowdown in the
economy. 
</P>
</TEXT>
