<HEADLINE> S. African Reserves Up </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG, June 2 (Xinhua) -- The South African Reserve
Bank's (SARB) gross gold and foreign exchange reserves rose to
50.7 billion rand (7.2 billion U.S. dollars) at the end of May
from 50.0 billion rand (7 billion dollars) at the end of April,
the SARB said on Friday.
</P>
<P>
The utilization of foreign credit lines amounted to 17.1
billion rand (2. 4 billion dollars) at the end of May from 16.7
billion rand (2.3 billion dollars) at the end of April.
</P>
<P>
The outstanding oversold forward book of the Bank fell to 15.1
billion dollars at the end of May from 15.2 billion dollars at the
end of April, while the net open foreign currency position (NOFP)
remained unchanged at 10.2 billion dollars at the close of
business on May 31, 2000.
</P>
<P>
Economists said earlier in the week that they expected gross
gold and foreign exchange reserves to total 51.2 billion rand (7.3
billion dollars), with the NOFP expected to come in unchanged
from its end-April 10.2 billion dollars level. 
</P>
</TEXT>
