<HEADLINE> China Makes Donation for OAU Peace-Keeping Mission </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ADDIS ABABA, June 2 (Xinhua) -- China Friday presented to the
Organization of African Unity (OAU) a donation of materials and
equipment that shall be used in peacekeeping missions in Africa.
</P>
<P>
Chinese Ambassador Jiang Zhengyun and Assistant
Secretary-General of the OAU Mahamat Habib Doutoum attended the
presentation ceremony and signed the documents.
</P>
<P>
Jiang said at the ceremony that the OAU has played an
irreplaceable role in the affirmation of political identity and
the realization of the unity of the continent.
</P>
<P>
"To make the OAU the vital instrument of the collective action
within Africa, we believe that the OAU Mechanism for Conflict
Prevention, Management and Resolution is a valuable asset for the
continent which must be nurtured and consolidated," he said.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese ambassador reiterated that China would continue
supporting, morally and materially, the OAU's tenacious efforts
in making and keeping peace in Africa.
</P>
<P>
On behalf of the OAU Secretary-General Salim Ahmed Salim,
Doutoum expressed appreciation of China's donation toward African
peace process.
</P>
<P>
He said, "This is not the first time that China has rendered
assistance in support of OAU efforts at conflict prevention,
management and resolution.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese government has made substantial financial
contribution to the (OAU) Peace Fund."
</P>
<P>
China's latest donation will enhance the capacity of OAU
military observers to undertake their peacekeeping operations
efficiently, he added.
</P>
<P>
China's donation to the OAU include, among others, tents,
beddings and field tools. 
</P>
</TEXT>
