<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Ceremonies Celebrate Birthday of General Zhang Xueliang </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHENYANG, June 2 (Xinhua) -- Hundreds of people held a ceremony
today to celebrate the 100th birthday of general Zhang Xueliang,
in the city of Haining, Zhang's birthplace, in northeast China's
Liaoning Province.
</P>
<P>
Zhang and General Yang Hucheng arrested Chiang Kai-shek, leader
of the Kuomintang (KMT), in the famous Xi'an Incident on December
12, 1936, which was eventually settled peacefully with the efforts
of the Communist Party of China (CPC), and which impelled Chiang
to fight together with the CPC against invading Japanese troops.
</P>
<P>
However, Zhang was imprisoned by Chiang soon after the incident,
and spent decades under house arrest in Taiwan under the KMT until
recent years, and General Yang was tortured to death in a KMT
prison in September 1949, just before the founding of the People's
Republic of China.
</P>
<P>
Relatives of Zhang and Yang were invited to attend today's
ceremony. The city also sent telegraphs and representatives to
congratulate Zhang in Hawaii, where the general is now living.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
