<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Seriously Injured Dolphin Rescued in China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 2 (Xinhua) -- A seriously injured Pacific dolphin
found on the beach of Dongshan Island in east China's Fujian
Province was saved Wednesday by local experts.
</P>
<P>
The dolphin was driven on to the beach by the tide and could
not return to the sea because of injuries, according to today's
Liberation Army Daily.
</P>
<P>
When local fishermen found it on May 30, the dolphin was
actually on the verge of death.
</P>
<P>
Upon learning the news, local military medical workers and
civilian medical personnel immediately launched a rescue operation
to save the mammal.
</P>
<P>
The dolphin, seven or eight years old, 2.4 meters long, and
weighing 120 kilograms, is still under special care at a local
oceanarium.
</P>
<P>
Dolphins are listed as one of the world's second-class
endangered species.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
