<DATE_TIME> 2000-06-02 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Middle East Economic Briefs </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CAIRO, June 2 (Xinhua) -- The following are economic briefs from
the Middle East countries.
</P>
<P>
ANKARA -- Turkish employers and workers began to pay
unemployment insurance as of June 1, reported Anatolia News Agency
on Friday.
</P>
<P>
The unemployment insurance fund was introduced in accordance
with the Social Security Reform Law adopted by the Grand National
Assembly (Parliament) on August 25, 1999.
</P>
<P>
Employees, who enjoy social security guarantees, are supposed to
pay a 2 percent monthly cut from their wages to the fund while cuts
are 3 percent for their bosses.
</P>
<P>
Labor and Social Security Minister Yasar Okuyan said that the
introduction of the unemployment insurance fund is a revolution in
the work force.
</P>
<P>
JERUSALEM -- Israel is expected to score a growth rate of 4
percent this year, Bank of Israel predicted.
</P>
<P>
Total foreign exchange reserve in May stood at 22.216 billion U.
S. dollars, up by 2.99 percent from 21.552 billion dollars the same
period of last year.
</P>
<P>
SANAA -- The total foreign exchange reserve in Bank of Yemen
scored an all-time high of 2 billion U.S. dollars by May.
</P>
<P>
Banking sources said the reserve can meet the needs of imports
for at least six months.
</P>
<P>
The surge was mainly attributed to the rising oil prices in
world market, a budget surplus in the past four months of 25
billion riyals (155 million U.S. dollars), and to the reliable
economic and monetary policies carried out by the government in
cooperation with the International Monetary Fund (IMF) and the
World Bank.
</P>
<P>
Total foreign exchange reserve stood at 981 million dollars by
1998 before it mounted to 1.4 billion dollars in l999.
</P>
<P>
RABAT -- Morocco set up a second biggest insurance company in
the country based on a financial partnership between French AXSA
Group, which holds 51 percent of the company's capital, and
Moroccan UNA Group which holds the remaining 49 percent.
</P>
<P>
The new firm carries the AXSA Insurance Morocco title with a
basic capital of 3 billion dirhams (300 million U.S. dollars) and
reserve funds of 8.8 billion dirhams (870 million dollars).
</P>
<P>
The new firm is expected to hold 21 percent of local insurance
market by 1.1 billion U.S. dollars.
</P>
<P>
CAIRO -- Egyptians traded 30 tons of gold during the January-
April period, up from 25 tons during the corresponding period of
l999.
</P>
<P>
Minister of Supply and Internal Trade Hassan Ali Khedr said that
Egypt ranks the third in the Middle East and the seventh in the
world in terms of gold trade. It is one of the states which trade
over 100 tons of gold every year, he added. 
</P>
</TEXT>
