<BODY>
<HEADLINE> New Zealand Stocks Finish Higher </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WELLINGTON, June 2 (Xinhua) -- The New Zealand sharemarket
closed higher here Friday.
</P>
<P>
The NZSE40 Index ended 34 points higher at 2,027 with a
turnover of 83.8 million NZ dollars (38.2 million U.S. dollars).
</P>
<P>
Most leading stocks became stronger with Australia-New Zealand
Bank rising 50 cents to 1,535 cents, followed by AMP up 34 to 1,
970 cents.
</P>
<P>
Telecom gained 18 cents to 781 cents, Fletcher Energy 13 to 570
cents, Carter Holt Harvey 6 to 179 cents, and Sky TV 1 cent to 371
cents.
</P>
<P>
Tower, Fletcher Paper and Fletcher Building were up 5 cents
each to 585, 239 and 215 cents, respectively. 
</P>
</TEXT>
