<DOCNO> XIE20000602.0153 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-06-02 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Tourist Arrivals Down in Indonesia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JAKARTA, June 2 (Xinhua) -- The number of foreign tourists
visiting Indonesia were reportedly down by 0.94 percent in April
this year to 337,800 from 341,008 in March due to political
uncertainty in the country, the Central Bureau of Statistic (BPS)
said here Friday.
</P>
<P>
"But during January-April this year, the number of foreign
tourists visiting the country reached 1.3 millions or up by 4.05
percent compared to the same period last year," BPS Chairwoman
Sudarti Surbakti told a press conference.
</P>
<P>
She expected that security situation in Indonesia will be
getting better and better, "so there will be more foreign tourists
to visit here and (it will) bring Indonesia back to be one of the
tourist destinations."
</P>
<P>
The number of foreign tourists visiting Indonesia reached 3.9
million people in 1999 or up by 4.13 percent against the figure in
1998.
</P>
<P>
The Indonesian government has targeted to earn 5 billion U.S.
dollars from 5.1 million foreign tourists who are expected to
visit the country each year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE20000602.0154 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-06-02 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Sharif Indicted in Helicopter Case </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, June 2 (Xinhua) -- Pakistan's accountability court
at Attock Fort, 80 kilometers west of Islamabad, Friday indicted
former Prime Minister Nawaz Sharif in a helicopter reference.
</P>
<P>
The National Accountability Bureau has filed a case against the
deposed premier in connection with the private purchase of a
Russia-made helicopter in 1993.
</P>
<P>
The prosecution says that Sharif failed to mention the
helicopter, which he had purchased for private use, in his Income
Tax returns. Sharif has denied the accusation.
</P>
<P>
Three witnesses, including the helicopter pilot Sajid Latif,
were summoned Friday on the request of prosecution. However, their
statements were not recorded.
</P>
<P>
The court will resume hearing on June 9.
</P>
<P>
Sharif's indictment in the helicopter case coincided with the
Sindh High Court's acceptance of prosecution appeal for regular
hearing, demanding death penalty for him in the plane hijacking
case.
</P>
<P>
Sharif was accused of denying the landing in Karachi of a
civilian plane which the then army chief and now chief executive
General Pervez Musharraf was on board.
</P>
<P>
The Anti-Terrorism Court in Karachi convicted in the hijacking
case in April and awarded him life imprisonment. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
