<DOCNO> XIE20000602.0160 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-06-02 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> S. Africa, Sweden Sign Defense Agreement </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG, June 2 (Xinhua) -- South Africa and Sweden on
Friday signed an agreement on defence co-operation which would
include peacekeeping and logistics.
</P>
<P>
Endorsing the agreement at the South African Defence Force
headquarters in Pretoria, Defence Minister Mosiuoa Lekota said in
a statement that the aim of the agreement was to meet and maintain
the technological demands, capabilities and standards of the new
millennium in the defence force.
</P>
<P>
"We are like Siamese twins in so many ways going through
similar baptism," Lekota said.
</P>
<P>
He said South Africa's defence and security policy had a
national and international dimension.
</P>
<P>
"While an outright military offensive against us may be
remote, in military terms anything is possible and it would,
therefore, be exceedingly naive and embarrassing to be caught
snoozing," he said.
</P>
<P>
He said South Africa's policy was defensive, deterrent,
politico- diplomatic and human rights oriented.
</P>
<P>
Concerning cooperation and collaboration with other states at
international level, he said: "We actively participate in the
peaceful resolution of conflicts, diplomatic intervention and
strengthening of democracy."
</P>
<P>
"We uphold respect for human rights without interference in
the internal affairs of our neighbors, participate actively in the
affairs of the United Nations, the Organization of African Unity
and the Southern African Development Community," he said.
</P>
<P>
He said it was important to control and reduce the spread of
conflicts for the benefit of South Africa, the Southern African
Development Community region and Sweden.
</P>
<P>
"We therefore disapprove vehemently of dictatorships and coup
d'etats as they constitute a flagrant recipe for political
instability with disastrous results to the inhabitants of the
whole region." 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
