<HEADLINE> S. Africa to Join UN Peacekeeping Force in Congo </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG, June 2 (Xinhua) -- South Africans would probably
join the UN peacekeeping process in the Democratic Republic of the
Congo (DRC) in about two weeks' time, Foreign Affairs
director-general Sipho Pityana said on Friday.
</P>
<P>
South Africa was working to deploy specialized elements for
peacekeeping duties in the DRC by June 17, he told reporters in
Pretoria.
</P>
<P>
Pityana said these elements would include teams to deal with
air traffic control, fire-fighting, handling of air cargo and
medical emergencies. 
</P>
</TEXT>
