<DOCNO> XIE20000602.0162 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-06-02 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> ASP for China's Building Industry to Operate </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 2 (Xinhua) -- The Hong Kong-based Coastal
International Group and its subsidiary, eBuilds Technology Limited,
announced recently they will open the ebuilds.net website this
year to provide business-to-business e-commerce as an application
software provider (ASP).
</P>
<P>
This will be the first application software provider (ASP) in
China's building industry.
</P>
<P>
ASP is a recently emerging service item which provides internal
management and application software that is incorporated into the
user's business management system. Traditional network companies
provide only e-commmerce platform which only create an exterior
environment and handle external affairs.
</P>
<P>
Experts agreed that the opening of the new network will speed
up the development of e-commerce in China's building industry, and
significantly improve the level of management of construction
enterprises.
</P>
<P>
Coastal International has diversified expertise and ten years
of experience in the building industry, consultancy, and business
management.
</P>
<P>
Ebuilds.net will offer various online services for developers,
builders, and sub-contractors. Along with industry-related
information, the website will also provide computer management
application software covering the entire process of a project
through the Internet, as well as management, maintenance, and the
upgrading of services for the system.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
