<HEADLINE> Sino-Japanese Pharmaceutical-Monitoring Project Launched </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 2 (Xinhua) -- A Sino-Japanese pharmaceutical-
monitoring project was launched here today with a signing ceremony
between the State Drug Administration and the Japanese embassy to
China.
</P>
<P>
During the five years of the project, the State Drug
Administration and the Japanese International Cooperation Agency (
JICA) will conduct activities including Japan sending experts to
China, China sending students to Japan, and Japan providing China
with pharmaceutical-monitoring equipment, so as to promote the
security of medicines in China. 
</P>
