<HEADLINE> Pipeline Fire Kills 5, Injures 1 in Southwestern Iran </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN, June 2 (Xinhua) -- At least five people were killed and
another was injured on Friday morning in an oil pipeline fire in
Khorramabad, Iran's southwestern Lorestan province.
</P>
<P>
The Islamic Republic News Agency reported that five passengers
on a Nissan car who were riding on a nearby road were burnt to
death when their car caught fire. A fireman was sent to hospital
due to severe burns.
</P>
<P>
The casualties occurred when an oil pipeline, 10 kilometers
south of the provincial capital of Khorramabad caught fire at 0700
hours local time (02:30 GMT) Friday.
</P>
<P>
The cause of the incident is under investigation. 
</P>
</TEXT>
