<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Philippine Stocks Rise Strongly </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, June 2 (Xinhua) -- Share prices in the Philippine Stock
Exchange rose strongly Friday on expectations the United States
Federal Reserve would not anymore raise U.S. key rates
aggressively this year.
</P>
<P>
The 30-company Phisix, the market's main index, rose 42.22
points, or 2.87 percent, to close at 1,512.75. The broader all
share index was also up by 7.75 points to 636.55.
</P>
<P>
Dealers exchanged 748 million shares worth some 28.4 million U.
S.dollars on Friday against Thursday's 2 billion shares worth some
22 million dollars.
</P>
<P>
Analysts said investors positioned in high-capitalized issues
are confident the U.S. economy has showed signs of slowing down
after the series of U.S. rates hikes early this year.
</P>
<P>
On Friday's trading, the most active shares were those of
Philippine Long Distance Telephone Company, Ayala Corporation and
Manila Electric Company. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
