<DOCNO> XIE20000602.0170 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-06-02 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Indonesia Posts 0.84 Percent Inflation in May </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JAKARTA, June 2 (Xinhua) -- Chairwoman of Indonesia's Central
Bureau of Statistic (BPS) Sudarti Surbakti announced here Friday
that Indonesia posted a 0.84 percent inflation in May, higher than
the 0.56 percent in April.
</P>
<P>
The inflation rate during January-May this year reached 2.35
percent, she said.
</P>
<P>
Surbakti said that of the seven groups of consumers goods
mentioned in the consumer price index, five groups were in the
grip of inflation, with housing registering a 1.84 percent rise,
clothing 0.85 percent, healthy 0.40 percent, and education,
recreation and sports 0.81 percent, while transportation and
communication rose 2.47 percent.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the other two groups, namely the food group and the
group of processed food, drinks, cigarette and tobacco, were
recorded to have undergone deflation by 0.03 percent and 0.09
percent, respectively, Surbakti said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
