<DOCNO> XIE20000602.0175 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-06-02 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Tanzanian Bus Accident Kills 10, Injures 38 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DAR ES SALAAM, June 2 (Xinhua) -- Ten people, including an
American tourist, were killed and 38 others seriously injured when
the bus they were taking overturned Thursday morning in Tanzania's
southwestern Mbeya Region.
</P>
<P>
Newspapers here quoted the Mbeya Regional Police Commander
Laurian Sanya as saying that the bus, which was traveling from
Mbeya town to Sumbawanga town in the neighboring Rukwa Region
overturned at around 6:00 in the morning after the driver failed
to control it.
</P>
<P>
According to the police commander, six victims, including the
driver of the ill-fated bus, died on the spot, while four others
died shortly after reaching a local hospital for treatment.
</P>
<P>
He identified the deceased U.S. tourist as Natalie Dyck, a
22-year-old college student from California.
</P>
<P>
He said investigations on the cause of the accident are still
going on, but preliminary reports hint that the bus, carrying more
than 55 passengers, exceeded the speed limit. 
</P>
</TEXT>
