<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Kenya's Tourism Sector Earns More </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NAIROBI, June 2 (Xinhua) -- Kenya's earnings from tourism
increased by 21.7 percent to 21.3 billion shillings (about 288
million U.S. dollars) in 1999 against 21.3 billion shillings
(about 236 million dollars) in the previous year, the latest
statistics indicated.
</P>
<P>
The good performance was due to concerted efforts of the entire
tourism industry in the national spirit of unity, Friday's East
African Standard daily quoted Kenya's Tourism, Trade and Industry
Minister Nicholas Biwott as saying.
</P>
<P>
Tourism, the third largest foreign exchange earner in the east
African country, has been picking up in the last two years
following a downturn since early 1990s. 
</P>
</TEXT>
