<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China Takes Bold Steps to Boost Auto Sales </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 2 (Xinhua) -- The Chinese government today
announced the cancellation of 238 types of charges related to
transportation and vehicles as of July 1, in a bold move to
encourage sales of motor vehicles.
</P>
<P>
A press release from the Ministry of Finance said this move
could save vehicle owners and operators up to 14.5 billion yuan a
year.
</P>
<P>
A detailed list of canceled charges are contained in a circular
jointly issued by the Ministry of Finance and the State
Development Planning Commission, and approved by the State Council.
</P>
<P>
This latest move is expected to further standardize the order
of government distribution, reduce the burdens on institutions and
ordinary people, boost motor vehicle buying, and create conditions
for the reform of the transportation and vehicle taxation systems,
the circular said. 
</P>
