<P>
JAKARTA -- At least two civilians were killed while three
others injured in a fresh communal bloodshed on Thursday in Ambon,
capital of Indonesia's Maluku province, a report reaching here
said Friday.
</P>
<P>
It said that the fresh clashes took place on Jl AY Patty and
Jalan AM Sangadji. The victims were believed to have been shot by
snipers, the report said. Commander of the Pattimura Regional
Military, Brig. Gen. Max Tamaela confirmed the incident, saying
that his side had arrested one of his own troops believed to have
acted as a sniper during the riot. (Indonesia-Violence)
