</P>
<P>
BERLIN -- German Chancellor Gerhard Schroeder told U.S.
president Bill Clinton, who is currently on a week-long European
tour, that the U.S. National Missile Defense (NMD) system could
spark a new round of global arms race.
</P>
<P>
After a two-hour talk with Clinton, Shroeder told reporters
that he is worried over U.S. development of the NMD system and his
country will do whatever it can to deter any possible global arms
race sparked by the NMD. He said he also exchanged views on the
current Russian situation with Clinton before his upcoming visit
to Russia, part of his European trip. Both sides indicated they
have common interests in supporting Russia as a politically and
economically stable partner of the west. (Germany-US-NMD)
</P>
