<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Israeli-Palestinian Teams to Discuss Jerusalem in Nicosia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NICOSIA, June 2 (Xinhua) -- Israeli and Palestinian negotiators
will kick off a three-day meeting here Friday on the future status
of Jerusalem, within the framework of an overall solution to the
Arab-Israeli problem.
</P>
<P>
Local media reports said the two sides are expected to deal with
issues concerning the future status of Jerusalem, expressing "their
interests, fears and anxieties" over the issue.
</P>
<P>
Each side will send seven to eight representatives who are "very
close to leadership" to the meetings, including diplomats,
officials dealing with security matters and experts.
</P>
<P>
Israel seized the Arab eastern part of Jerusalem in the 1967
Middle East war. It insists that Jerusalem is its eternal and
indivisible capital, while the Palestinians want East Jerusalem as
the capital of their future independent state.
</P>
<P>
The final status of the Holy City, widely acknowledged as one of
the thorniest issues in the entire peace process, is to be decided
in the final-status talks between Israel and the Palestinians.
</P>
<P>
Cyprus News Agency quoted reliable sources as saying that the
talks will be the start of a "dialogue" between the two sides that
would pave the way for future negotiations.
</P>
<P>
The meeting is organized by the Jerusalem-based Israeli-
Palestinian Center for Research and Information.
</P>
<P>
A member of the Swedish Social Democratic party will act as a
mediator during the talks. Sweden has sponsored similar contacts in
the past between Israel and the Palestinians.
</P>
<P>
Cyprus has repeatedly expressed its wish and readiness to play
host to meetings between the parties involved in the Middle East
peace process, in a bid to contribute to the efforts for an overall
settlement. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
