<HEADLINE> Major Ship-Building Contract Signed in Tianjin </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TIANJIN, June 2 (Xinhua) -- Shipbuilding companies in the port
city of Tianjin in north China recently signed their biggest
contracts ever, with Denmark and South Africa, worth a combined
100 million US dollars.
</P>
<P>
According to the deal, the Tianjin Machinery Import and Export
Group (TMIEG) and the Tianjin Xingang Shipyard will produce six 32,
000-ton bulk cargo ships for the Clipper Group of Denmark and the
Unicorn Company of South Africa.
</P>
<P>
The TMIEG has built and rebuilt container and bulk cargo ships
for Canada, Japan, Russia, Ukraine, and other countries.
</P>
<P>
