<HEADLINE> Rapid Increase of Foreign Trade in North China Province </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHIJIAZHUANG, June 2 (Xinhua) -- According to the latest
statistics, north China's Hebei Province achieved 1.23 billion U.S.
dollars of export and import trade during the past five months of
this year, up 23.2 percent over the same period of last year.
</P>
<P>
Analysts say that better export structure and an improved
investment environment account for the foreign trade increase.
</P>
<P>
The province established relationships with more agents and
dealers in the U.S., Europe, and Japan, who helped Hebei's
products enter large shopping malls and chain stores in those
countries. The province also adjusted its products in a timely
fashion, according to frequent feedback from the overseas markets.
</P>
<P>
Statistics show that the export of clothing, steel, and pottery
to European Union countries, the U.S., Japan, Hong Kong, and South
Korea continued to rise over the past five months.
</P>
<P>
Foreign investment reached 520 million U.S. dollars, up 23
percent over last year. Investment from the U.S., South Korea, and
Taiwan increased by 31 percent, 21 percent and 41 percent,
respectively, for the period. 
</P>
</TEXT>
