<HEADLINE> South China Customs Stems Drug Smuggling </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUANGZHOU, June 2 (Xinhua) -- The Gongbei Customs, the closest
to the special administrative region of Macao, has intensified
passenger security checks in an effort to stem drug smuggling.
</P>
<P>
The customs in south China's Guangdong Province has reported 28
drug smuggling cases involving 177 grams of narcotics, since the
start of this year.
</P>
<P>
On May 8, a Macao resident surnamed Huang was discovered
carrying 4.36 grams of heroin and 15.35 grams of other narcotics
in his mouth and anus.
</P>
<P>
He confessed that he bought the drug for himself and intended
to bring it to Macao.
</P>
<P>
The customs found that most of the drug traffickers are Hong
Kong and Macao residents.  
</P>
