<DOCNO> XIE20000602.0236 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-06-02 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Sino-Myanmar Anniversary Ties Photo Exhibition Opens in Myanmar </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
YANGON, June 2 (Xinhua) -- A grand photos and pictures
exhibition in celebration of the golden jubilee of diplomatic
relations between China and Myanmar opened at the City Hall here
Friday.
</P>
<P>
The opening ceremony of the exhibition, jointly sponsored by
the Chinese embassy and the Myanmar Information Ministry, was
attended by Chinese ambassador Liang Dong, third secretary of the
Myanmar State Peace and Development Council Lieutenant-General Win
Myint, foreign minister U Win Aung and four other ministers.
</P>
<P>
Present on the occasion were also foreign diplomats in Myanmar
as well as representatives of Myanmar-Chinese and Chinese
residents in the country.
</P>
<P>
The exhibition displays 150 sheets of photos which cover three
contents -- exchange of visits by the two countries' leaders,
economic cooperation and social and cultural relations between the
two countries.
</P>
<P>
Speaking at the opening ceremony, Chinese ambassador Liang Dong
said China and Myanmar are good neighbors linked by common
mountains and rivers, adding that the pauk-phau (fraternal)
friendship between the two countries can be traced back long in
history.
</P>
<P>
He noted that Myanmar is among the countries that first
established diplomatic relations with China and the first one that
signed the boundary treaty with China.
</P>
<P>
"Our two countries jointly advocated the Five Principles of
Peaceful Co-existence in the international community, and
maintained close cooperation and mutual support in many
international affairs," he recalled, adding that the exchange and
cooperation between the two countries in various fields were also
steadily developed and strengthened.
</P>
<P>
He expressed the belief that the display of true portrayals of
friendly exchanges between the two countries and peoples will be
conducive to the broadening of the knowledge about the history of
friendly exchanges between the two countries, to the strengthening
of mutual understanding and friendship between the two peoples and
to the further consolidation of confidence in building the Sino-
Myanmar friendly cooperative relations of good neighborliness and
mutual trust into the new century.
</P>
<P>
At the ceremony, Myanmar foreign minister U Win Aung said a new
chapter has been opened in the history of bilateral relations
between Myanmar and China since the two countries established
diplomatic relations fifty years ago and the bilateral relations
are always characterized by mutual friendship and understanding.
</P>
<P>
He noted that Myanmar and China were able to establish kinsfolk-
like relations between the two countries for being immediate
neighbors sharing a long common border and having close affinities
in culture, traditions and custom.
</P>
<P>
He appraised that the successful demarcation of the over 2,000-
kilometer-long boundary between the two countries was an important
milestone in the annals of the bilateral relations.
</P>
<P>
He also said Myanmar and China together with India are proud of
being co-founders of the Five Principles of Peaceful Co-existence
which are now regarded as important guiding principles in the
conduct of international relations.
</P>
<P>
He added that the exhibition witnesses how the leaders of the
two countries have relentlessly tried to maintain and further
strengthen the bilateral amicable ties to the mutual benefit of
the two countries and peoples.
</P>
<P>
The exhibition will last for three days.
</P>
<P>
China and Myanmar established diplomatic relations on June 8,
1950. 
</P>
</TEXT>
