<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
PANAMA -- Panama and the United States signed Thursday a
protocol that makes amends to Agreement regarding the Treaty and
Investment Protection singed on October 27, 1982, in Washington.
</P>
<P>
According to the protocol, at any moment after six months
following the date on which the difference comes forth on
Panamanian land, Panamanian or American investors can submit it
to conciliation or obliged arbitrage to international instances. (
Panama-US-Investment)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
OTTAWA -- Canada's benchmark TSE 300 composite index jumped 300.
21 points Thursday to finish at 9552.20, a level TSE hardly held
for days for the past two months.
</P>
<P>
