market research firms have found small business owners in the
United States are increasingly taking their businesses online and
purchasing online.
</P>
<P>
An annual survey conducted by Dun &AMP; Bradstreet (D&AMP;B) in
February and March of 2000 found that 40 percent of the small
businesses have their own Web sites, up from just over a quarter
last year, and that 70 percent now have Internet access. (US-Small
Businesses)
</P>
