<HEADLINE> China Sees Surging Foreign Trade in Jan-April </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 2 (Xinhua) -- China's foreign trade has been
growing on a fast track in the first four months this year with
trade volume totaling 137.1 billion U.S. dollars, up 38.8 percent
year on year, a senior official said here today.
</P>
<P>
Qiu Xiaohua, deputy director of the National Bureau of
Statistics, said at a news conference that total export during the
period amounted to 72.2 billion U.S. dollars, surging 39 percent,
with import increasing 38.6 percent to reach 64.9 billion U.S.
dollars.
</P>
<P>
The four months saw a trade surplus of 7.4 billion U.S. dollars,
2.2 billion more than that of the same period last year. 
</P>
