<HEADLINE> German Funds to Boost China's Western Development </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 2 (Xinhua) -- The German Government Thursday
agreed to provide 90 million U.S.dollars to help China's west
areas as well as the country's environmental protection and
poverty-relief drive, today's China Daily reported.
</P>
<P>
According to the agreement signed Thursday afternoon in
Beijing, Germany will provide 70 million U.S. dollars in financial
cooperation funds.
</P>
<P>
Most of those funds will be invested in China's western regions
where road construction and health care will enjoy top priority.
</P>
<P>
Also with the money, more trees will be planted in the
mountainous regions of Hebei Province, where the German Government
has funded local afforestation efforts for more than ten years.
</P>
<P>
In the technical field, Germany will provide 20 million U.S.
dollars to help China's western regions develop their vocational
education.
</P>
<P>
Ten percent of those funds is for China's free use and the rest
is for 40-year-long preferential loans.
</P>
<P>
Official statistics show that Germany has provided two billion
U.S. dollars and 90 million U.S. dollars in the financial and
technical cooperation fields respectively, since the country began
providing loans to China in 1981.  
</P>
