<HEADLINE> Holyfield-Ruiz WBA Title Fight Postponed </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, June 1 (Xinhua) The fight on June 10 between
Evander Holyfield and John Ruiz for the heavyweight title have
been postponed because of a training injury to Holyfield, the
World Boxing Association heavyweight said Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Holyfield suffered a rib injury during workouts in Houston. He
was set to try and become a world champion for the fourth time
here at Caesar's Palace by claiming the piece of the world crown
stripped from Britain's Lennox Lewis.
</P>
<P>
Holyfield, 37, has a 36-4 record with one draw, that a
controversial outcome against Lewis in New York in March of last
year that enabled him to keep his crowns until Lewis took them
with a unanimous decision in Las Vegas last November.
</P>
<P>
Promoter Don King had been trying to stage this bout since he
went to court in New York and had Lewis stripped of the WBA crown
for facing Grant instead of Ruiz, the dubious top-rated contender
of the WBA and one of three King fighters the WBA had ranked as
its top challengers. 
</P>
