<HEADLINE> HK Bank Confident in Chinese Market After WTO Entry </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, June 2 (Xinhua) -- The Hong Kong and Shanghai Banking
Corporation (HSBC) plans to increase the number of its employees
in China's interior from 800 to more than 1,000 over the next five
years.
</P>
<P>
Eddie Wong, president of the bank's China business, said the
decision was only part of HSBC's effort to increase its presence
in the interior.
</P>
<P>
"China's anticipated entry into the World Trade Organization (
WTO) represents more opportunities and challenges," Wong said. "We
are preparing for both."
</P>
<P>
Wong said that HSBC has full confidence in its development in
the interior and has therefore moved its China headquarters from
Hong Kong to Shanghai.
</P>
<P>
According to Wong, the bank will expand its cooperation with
local banks in such areas as Chinese currency business and
Internet banking.  
</P>
