<DATE_TIME> 2000-06-02 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Subtropical Golden Monkey Bred In NE China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HARBIN, June 2 (Xinhua) -- A couple of golden monkeys have
produced babies three times in the Harbin Zoo, northeast China's
Heilongjiang Province, since they arrived here in 1992.
</P>
<P>
This couple of golden monkeys, a kind of subtropical animal,
had their first baby in Harbin in 1995, which is also the first
time that golden monkeys have babies in cool temperate zone.
</P>
<P>
What surprises people most is that both of the golden monkeys
are in their old age, the husband is 17 years old and the wife 19.
The natural life expectancy for golden monkey ranges from 18 to 22
years old.
</P>
<P>
Such golden-coated monkey mainly live in the subtropical area
in southwest China, and is a typical wild animal to the country.
This animal is under state first-grade protection because of its
very small number.
</P>
<P>
Sources from the zoo said considering the fact that the golden
monkeys love to rest on trees and are fear of contacting human
beings, workers in the zoo build special houses, as high as seven
meters above the ground level, for them, so that they can avoid
mis-birth caused by dread.
</P>
<P>
Workers also choose September and October as the time for
golden monkeys to cohabit and get pregnant, thus preventing them
from giving births in severe winter.
</P>
<P>
Workers also feed them with nutritious foods such as peanut,
eggs and Chinese dates and moderate Chinese medicines during their
pregnant period to help golden monkeys improve immunity in cold
environment.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE20000602.0295 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-06-02 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> More Overseas Tourists Flock to Guangxi </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NANNING, June 2 (Xinhua) -- A total of 333,000 overseas
tourists visited south China's Guangxi Zhuang Autonomous Region
from January to April this year.
</P>
<P>
The number of overseas arrivals went up by 77.5 percent from
the same period last year, a record high, said local sources.
</P>
<P>
Guangxi Zhuang Autonomous Region is bounded by Yunnan Province
on the west, Guizhou on the north, Hunan on the northeast, and
Guangdong on the southeast, and by Vietnam and the Beibu Bay on
the southwest.
</P>
<P>
With an area of 236,661 square kilometers, Guangxi is unique in
China that is located along coast, border and big rivers. Guangxi
is also a place where many of China's ethnic groups such as Zhuang,
Miao, Yao, Maonan, Gin live.
</P>
<P>
The predominance of limestone gives many parts of Guangxi a
spectacular type of landscape, known to geographers as "karst", in
which pinnacles and spires, caves and caverns, sinkholes, and
subterranean streams abound. Picturesque rocky hills, spires of
grotesque proportions, strangely shaped caves, and all manner of
stalactites and stalagmites can be seen in many parts of this
region.
</P>
<P>
Among them, the most famous is Guilin City, which has a history
of more than 2,000 years and is renowned for its green mountains,
clear water and strangely-shaped stone formations.
</P>
<P>
Yuan Fenglan, vice chairman of Guangxi Zhuang Autonomous
Regional Government, pledged that they would make greater efforts,
including intensified promotion campaigns and construction of
infrastructure, to explore rich tourism resources in Guangxi's
countryside and attract more tourists to those places. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE20000602.0296 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-06-02 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Trunk Avenue in Beijing Prolonged </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 2 (Xinhua) -- Beijing has started a project to
prolong the Chang'an Street, key avenue in the capital.
</P>
<P>
When the project completes at the end of this year, the street
will be extended from present 13 kilometers to 45 km, said Wang
Guangtao, vice-mayor of Beijing.
</P>
<P>
The project includes 310,000 square meters of pavement, a six-
meter-wide green belt and an automatic traffic system.
</P>
<P>
Chang'an Street is the thoroughfare along which Tiananmen,
Forbidden City and Zhongnanhai, site of the Central Government,
are located. And it serves as the venue of many important
political and diplomatic events.
</P>
<P>
The municipal government of Beijing renovated the street last
year to mark the country's 50th founding anniversary. Key section
of the street has been widened to 50 meters. 
</P>
</TEXT>
