<P>
WASHINGTON -- A U.S. federal appeals court Thursday ruled in
favor of the father of Cuban boy Elian Gonzalez, saying the boy is
not entitled to a political asylum hearing.
</P>
<P>
The three-judge panel of the 11th U.S. Circuit Court of Appeals
in Atlanta said the Immigration and Naturalization Service's
decision that only a parent can act for his 6-year-old child in
immigration matters "comes within the range of reasonable choices.
" (US-Cuban Boy)
