<BODY>
<HEADLINE> European Major Stocks Surge On Tech Shares </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, June 2 (Xinhua) -- Europe's major stock markets ended
higher Friday after a U.S. economic report suggested the U.S.
economy may be cooling from its heady pace and ease pressure on
interest rates.
</P>
<P>
London's FTSE 100 index soared 155.9 points, or 2.4 percent, to
6,617.8. The blue-chip index gained 6.6 percent for the week.
</P>
<P>
The top 10 percentage gainers were in the technology, media and
telecom sectors Computer services firm CMG rose 18.43 percent,
Baltimore Technology soared 13.6 percent, Reuters Group leapt 16.1
percent and microchip designer ARM Holdings rose 12.3 percent.
</P>
<P>
Hand-held device maker Psion rose 13.3 percent, Colt Telecom
jumped 10.6 percent and mU.S.ic label EMI Group rose 10.3 percent.
</P>
<P>
The pan-European FTSE Europtop 300 was up 2.2 percent at 1,650.
67. Its information technology sub-index soared 9.5 percent and
the media sub-index jumped 5.7 percent.
</P>
<P>
German shares closed higher as weaker-than expected U.S. jobs
data eased rate fears. The benchmark DAX index closed 2.29 percent
or 166.19 points higher at 7,438.95, rising 500.62 from seven days
ago.
</P>
<P>
The CAC-40 index in Paris closed up 73.81 points, or 1.1
percent, to 6,673.52, its second straight record close though down
from its intra-session highs. For the week, the French index rose
8.9 percent. 
</P>
