<HEADLINE> Famous Russian Eye Surgeon Killed in Helicopter Crash </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, June 2 (Xinhua) -- Famous Russian eye surgeon
Svyatoslav Fyodorov and three other people died Friday in a
helicopter crash in northwest Moscow, Russian media reported.
</P>
<P>
The chopper, which belonged to Fyodorov's Eye Microsurgery
Center,crashed onto wasteland near Svetlogorsky Proyezd at about 7:
45 p.m.local time (15:45 GMT). All victims died instantly.
</P>
<P>
Fyodorov, 72, came to prominence in the 1970s after a series of
pioneering eye operations.
</P>
<P>
Preliminary data indicated that the crash was caused by
technical malfunction, the Itar-Tass news agency reported, citing
a police source.
</P>
<P>
Besides his professional and commercial success, Fyodorov also
engaged himself in the country political life. He ran for
president in 1996 but dropped out in the first round with a little
more than one percent of the vote. 
