<HEADLINE> Venezuelan Oil Closes Week at 27.13 Dlrs </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CARACAS, June 2 (Xinhua) -- The price of Venezuelan oil closed
the week at 27.13 U.S. dollars per barrel, 0.68 dollars above last
week's price, said the Mines and Energy Ministry (MEM) Friday.
</P>
<P>
The average price for the first five months of this year is 24.
86 dollars per barrel, a figure that leaves far behind the 16.07
dollars of 1999 and the 10.57 dollars of 1998, when the oil barrel
quotation collapsed.
</P>
<P>
The median for the price of the barrel of oil for the first
quarter of 2000 was 25.40 dollars, a figure that, according to the
experts, should drop slightly in the second quarter as a result of
the decision of the Organization of Petroleum Exporting Countries
(OPEC), of which Venezuela is one of its founding members, to
increase production to reduce its high price.
</P>
<P>
The OPEC decided to control the prices through increases of
cuts in the production in such a manner that they will fluctuate
within an upper band of 28 dollars and a lower one of 22 dollars.
</P>
<P>
Oil contributes 70 percent of the hard currency for Venezuela
and about 50 percent of the income for the national budget.
</P>
</TEXT>
